### 4.

1\. Now at that time Bhikkhus, who had rendered themselves liable to be
thrown back to the commencement (of their probationary course) <span
id="fr_723"></span>[2](#fn_705.md), used to

<span id="page_394">p. 394</span>

accept reverence \[&c., as before in chapter 1, reading throughout
'Bhikkhus liable to be thrown back to the beginning of their
probationary course' for 'Bhikkhus who had been placed on
probation <span id="fr_724"></span>[1](#fn_706.md);' and omitting in
chapter 2 the announcements referred to there in our note\].

